http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Tiruchirapalli/Tangedco-approves-power-development-scheme/article14018973.ece

The Tamil Nadu Generation and Distribution Corporation (Tangedco) has approved Integrated Power Development Scheme (IPDS) for improving power infrastructure in 522 statutory towns, including 81 towns in delta districts.It will be implemented with the contribution of Union and State governments and Tangedco. The Ministry of Power will be the primary source of fund.It has formed a monitoring committee to implement the scheme and it has permitted Tangedco to execute the projects on department or partial turnkey basis.It is estimated that it would cost Rs. 1,561.31 crore to implement the scheme in 522 towns, spread across 31 circles.In Tiruchi region, 81 towns in Pudukottai, Thanjavur, Tiruchi, Tiruvarur, Nagapattinam, and Karur districts have been selected for implementing the project at an estimate of Rs. 225.14 crore.Sources told The Hindu that out of 81 towns, the scheme would cover 22 towns in Thanjavur district and 16 towns in Tiruchi district. In Karur, the scheme would be implemented in 12 towns. It would cover eight towns each in Pudukottai, Tiruvarur, Perambalur, and Nagapattinam districts.It is proposed for strengthening sub-transmission network (HT/LT lines), including establishment of new 33/11 kV substations, augmentation of existing substations, carrying out Repair and Maintenance works in existing substations, bay extension, and installation of capacitor banks and others. Replacement of 3.24 lakh existing electro mechanical meters by static meters, erection of LT feeders for 295 km and LT network augmentation to the length of 419 km were among the scheme.It is to be implemented within 30 months, including a six-month window for procurement of material.